    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-03-15T15:48:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-03-15T15:48:00-05:00" n="225"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d225">
                <head>225. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Mission at the United Nations</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d225fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 974.7301/3–1557. Confidential; <gloss target="#t_Niact1"
                            >Niact</gloss>. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_DCD1"
                        >Dillon</persName>; cleared by <persName corresp="#p_HCA1"
                        >Herter</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_PH1">Phleger</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_RWM1">Rountree</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_ECB1"
                            >Elbrick</persName>; and approved by <persName corresp="#p_WFO1"
                            >Wilcox</persName> who signed for <persName corresp="#p_HCA1"
                            >Herter</persName>. Repeated Priority to Cairo. President <persName
                            corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> also approved the message; see
                            <ref target="#d226fn1">footnote 1, <hi rend="italic">infra.</hi>
                        </ref>
                    </note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1957-03-15T15:48:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 15, 1957—3:48 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>708. Re <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> 635<note n="2" xml:id="d225fn2">See
                            <ref target="#d222fn1">footnote 1, Document 222</ref>.</note> deliver
                    following orally to <gloss target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss>: <list>
                        <label>1.</label>
                        <item>It is highly important to get answer promptly from <persName
                                corresp="#p_NNNGA1">Nasser</persName> on interim arrangement re
                            canal, including payment of tolls, and <persName corresp="#p_HD1"
                                >Hammarskjold</persName> should press this point vigorously.</item>
                        <label>2.</label>
                        <item>U.S. stands on Four Power proposal. <persName corresp="#p_HD1"
                                >Hammarskjold</persName> should make every effort to obtain Egyptian
                            approval and should have no idea that U.S. will accept anything
                            less.</item>
                        <label>3.</label>
                        <item>If Egypt nevertheless rejects proposal, and makes counter proposal,
                                <persName corresp="#p_HD1">Hammarskjold</persName> should forward
                            such counter proposal to Four Powers promptly. He should in no event
                            attempt to negotiate any compromise himself.</item>
                        <label>4.</label>
                        <item>If Egypt makes no reply and attempts to open canal and collect 100
                            percent of tolls, determining unilaterally the disposition of the tolls,
                            U.S. would consider such action a violation of the six principles
                            adopted by Security Council and accepted by Egypt.</item>
                        <label>5.</label>
                        <item>
                            <persName corresp="#p_LHCJ1">Lodge</persName> can tell <persName
                                corresp="#p_HD1">Hammarskjold</persName> for his information only
                            that <persName corresp="#p_LHCJ1">Lodge</persName> assumes that if an
                            interim solution for canal satisfactory to U.S. is reached and if
                            agreement is reached on Gaza, U.S. would be prepared discuss
                            regularizing economic relations with Egypt.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HCA1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Herter</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
